content: My original rating was 3 stars as I only had it for a month.I am loving this app. I am able to create my own tasks, or use the pre programmed ones. The 20 min work 10 min break is awesome. If I haven't finished my task I can work through the break or continue on with the task after the break. Tasks can be scheduled with an Alarm, or made to reoccur. My only request would be to see a completed list. Just to progress in the app. Although I am seeing it in my houseüòÅ
Well..it hasn't updated in 4 years. (Edit: 8 years now.) I wouldn't buy something that doesn't regularly update.
The app is designed for an older version and may not function properly. Refunded ASAP

Works great to keep on track with everything. Would be amazing to have the "here's emergency cleaning" as a list bc it's the additional steps to get to the homepage and look that up. What'd also be nice to be able to use the pre-formulated tasks from challenges into your own list.
It used to be fine. Hasn't been updated in 6 years though and I don't think they have plans to maintain it. iOS app is way ahead of this one. Sad.
This would be more useful if the lists from the website were included. It's really just a random challenge generator.

Refund right after purchase. To create 'My List' I have to type things in one by one... will stick to my pen and paper method bc ain't nobody got time for that. If there was a check mark option for selecting common things in the house, that would be better suited for what I would like.
This helps me focus, gives me direction. Thank you so much for making this app.

I downloaded this app when it was free. Upgraded to pay and the app stopped working. Still no resolution as the app won't open. Plus many of the features I loved are gone. A huge disappointment after a wonderful start.

First Thank you for changing the name! It is a great app, but I hated the original name, esp. with 4 kids. So Thank You Thank You! Second, I am unable to update to the newer version of the app. I have a Samsung Galaxy Note 9s. Please help!
This app is the s%&t!!! If you like straight up talk then this is the right app. If you are easily offended, then keep looking.
Has not been updated in 6 years. I denied it looking at phone data and is working no issue.
I would love to see an update!
If I would just read the book and use the app!! I'd get so much done.
Love this! I wish you could choose how often you want a task to reoccur..unless I missed something? And you should add before and after pictures to the achievement logs!

userName: BET WE CAN MAKE IT FUN!
content: I love the app in general (and the book) but started getting glitches on my device. When you get a break you can't just start break, have to cancel and go back and forth several times. same when the break is over. I tried to reinstall and nothing changed.

overall a great app that helps me with cleaning. would give it 5 stars if it weren't for one thing: the motivational thing calling you lazy is really not cool, because a lot of people using this app don't avoid cleaning their house because they're lazy, but because they're anxious; depressed; have executive dysfunction; are disabled; etc. so maybe that's a thing to think about. otherwise great as said.
Fantastic.

I would love it if I could see my completed list rather than just the day it says I completed it. That way I can go back and see just how much I accomplished as well as how long its been since I've clean something. This is the only complaint I have about the app. Please seriously consider tweaking it.

so far the best app out there that actually works better for me and my family! $2 is well worth it! Trust me it will not disappoint! Very few cuss words, doesn't yell at you audibly, only visually! If you can't handle that then don't download, simple as that! Gives great detail on what needs to be done without having to actually make a list!

I couldn't wait to buy this app when it was first released. Now I've a new device and will NOT be reinstalling, as it demands access to my call data. As noted by Sara, it is an outrageous requirement. Dumped from 5 stars to 1, until permissions insanity is addressed.
Wont even install. Refund time!
motivated
Life Sustaining!

My wife uses the app and asked me to install it so she could share her lists with me. I returned this immediately because the app doesn't include that basic functionality. This isn't worth paying for.
Good, but could be more useful. I'd love, for instance, a pre-made checklist based on the emergency cleaning method on the website.

Love this app, especially for the random challenges that keep me tidying things i forget. Reason for 3 stars? When using the 20/10 timer, the alarm starts blaring but its unwieldy to go through all your open apps to find the UFYH app. A notification or forcing it to the front when the alarm goes off would be super helpful, especially for someone who gets panic attacks at loud, shrill alarms like this or fire alarms.

The developers demand access to your call information, which is completely unnecessary for the functionality of the app and a blatant data grab. I can't believe I paid them for the privilege of having my personal call information monitored. Beware.
It would be a nice addition to be able to change the timer to a ratio that works best for you. I prefer an evenly split time on rest and work.

I would give it five stars if the timer worked properly. The app and the book have been helping me immensely. However the timer is incomplete. The premise is simple - work for 20 minutes, timer goes off, then rest for 10 and  repeat if desired. There's no way to stop it though - no cancel or stop button. I close down the app, then I'm out running errands and the timer begins beeping when the app is not open. It's really too bad. I tried asking on her Facebook page and my post was denied.

Overall, I like the app, and it's mature audience approach suits me well. However, like others, I do wish it had an option to set notifications to remind me to get off my ass. Customizable notifications (when, how many times a week, etc) would be great. Send me a random challenge a few times a week would be great! Also, for recurring tasks on my un-f&#! list, having them drop off or grey out until they need to be done again would be sooo helpful. I'd like to see those customized too, in terms of how often they recur; daily, every other day, weekly, etc. Looking forward to improvements!

Make the lists better. I like it. The random challenges are great, but I would love to easily make daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly lists easily. You can make a list, but you do not have the option of how frequently it repeats.

It's not bad, rather bland and I also wish the timer could be adjusted for 
those like my self unable to sustain 20min of doing anything due to 
physical limitations

Disappointed in the 20/10 timer, bought it a year ago and was disappointed 
that it froze after my first 10 minute break and was stuck at 0:00. 
Frustrating to have to back out of it and restart it. The more I fiddle 
with my phone, the more likely I am to give up and start browsing. I 
reinstalled it this year, hoping it's be fixed, but I was still very 
disappointed today. Okay app, just wished the 20/10 timer worked better
ufyh has literally changed my life. I'm better than my mess!

I like it, I wish you could decide WHEN a task reoccurs. I've had it for 
months and just used it tonight. Hopefully all the issues with 
notifications are fixed that I've read in here.
Works great after the fix.
replyContent: We're working on a fix for that crash, and hope to have it out soon! Thank you for your feedback!

content:
I'm very grateful for the effort and thought put into making this app 
especially for females like me with ADHD

I've been using this app for years and I love it so much. I suffer from 
mental illness and trauma that makes day to day cleaning difficult 
sometimes, to the point where it piles up and seems unmanageable, but this 
app lets me get back in control. There are things I wouldnt even have 
thought of doing/cleaning that it reminds me to do. Its been well worth the 
small price. If you are just really bad at keeping up with cleaning to 
where it makes your mental health worse I highly recommend this app.

The app is well worth the tiny sum of money as a way to tip the author of 
the website / book, and the random challenge function is great. As a 
freestanding app it lacks some important functions, however. There is no 
way to set a task to recur after a certain period, so you have to choose 
between writing down repeating tasks like vacuuming every week or having 
them remain on the list when you click done. Being able to set recurring 
tasks that renew at a certain date would be a very useful addition.

There is a God. I'm so grateful that this app is back. It's not the flashiest of apps, but it's perfect for anyone who suffers from analysis paralysis and overwhelm when faced with a messy house. I was lost without it while it was gone from the Play Store.

Finally, it's back on Google play! The best kick in the pants for those who need help with housework, for those with ADD, for perfectionists who get overwhelmed, for anyone who wants to tackle chores in a sensible, funny way. YOU NEED THIS APP!
Fantastic app! I highly recommend it.
Love it!
Great in concept, but no ability to share the to do list with a roomate or SO, and the timer is quite inconstant with 20/10 and shutting off in the middle of the break.  Challenges are nice.

this app is great for what it does, and it has really motivated me to try to clean more!! I really appreciate (and am honestly impressed) that it was created and maintained despite such a small team that's so busy.
mostly useless without the lists. the timer alarm is hard to turn off.
This app makes life worth living. It has been with me for 3 phones and 2 apartments. I recommend it to everyone
Can you pretty please add a 45/15 timer and an emergency cleaning challenge? Thank you!
I need recurring reminders for daily, weekly, and monthly tasks and bills. please add on to the app. it's worth money to me. disabilities affect executive function.

I really love the blunt way this pushes me and implementing a system with breaks is more likely to stick. The only improvement I'd like to see is the ability to have a family option that allows each person to view the chores in their own devices and see if they've been done. It would also be great to be able to assign tasks to family members with due dates and times. Great app though!
Great app, but gave 4 stars due to malfunctioning 20/10 timer. Would give 5 for working timer.

Cool app, not sure it was worth buying but it was only $.99. But it definitely helps with keeping the house clean and cleaning the things you always forget to clean. I've used it for years now and always download it onto all of my other devices.
Hands down the most helpful app I've ever downloaded. Perfect for emergency-panic-in-laws-are-coming-cleaning!

I wanted to like this app. I deleted after receiving "TOMORROW YOU'LL BE ASHAMED AT HOW LAZY YOU WERE TODAY" as a motivational message. I get the tough love thing, but I don't need to be made to feel like garbage while trying to improve things. Overall, I wish this app was better. It essentially became a glorified timer and checklist. It definitely shouldn't cost money.
I like it, but I wish the Achievements section would update properly so I can feel some pride in completing my lists. :/

"Recurring" means more than once, but you cannot tell the app to remind you every day/week/whatever to do the chore. You have to put in a new "deadline" every time you reach the old deadline. You also cannot sort chores by deadline. Or if you can I can't find it. There are dozens of chore apps, this one is not worth paying for.
The idea is quite good and I enjoyed the 20/10 timer until I couldn't figure out how to turn it off, even after closing the app. I ultimately restarted my phone and then uninstalled the app.
I adore this app but wish you would offer a profanity free version I could recommend to my parents more shockable friends as they would love the functionality but wouldn't cope with the language!

Love this! It really eases some anxiety, especially if you usually have trouble feeling accomplished. I just wish it had a goal page, for things you'd like to strive for but can't be completed as quickly as a normal task.

So far I've only been using this app for the 20/10 timer, and while it does work reasonably well I suspect that I could write something that works better for that since there are a couple of issues. 1) at the end of the first break, the timer seems to stay on 0 when I try to start the next block of 20 minutes; I have to go out of the timer and back in to get it to reset the timer. 2) it uses the phone's ringtone as the alarm noise. It does let you change this from within the app but that also overrides the ringtone and does not make this clear. 3) with the phone on vibrate and headphones in, the alarm/ringtone sounds at full volume through both the headphones and the speaker. This is particularly an issue when using it in a public space (e.g. studying in a library). 4) the alarm can only be silenced by going into the app itself, nothing shows on the lock screen or in the notifications area to control it.

Great concept.  I'd love to be able to link it to Google Calendar or Google Fit.  I'd like to be able to set regular tasks, check off something I already did, or enter how much time I have to clean and have the app make suggestions.   I haven't found the right way to make this app work for me, but I still think it is a good product for people with ADD.
Best productivity app for me ever (and I'm F***ing lazy)

I love this app. The motivation and timer by themselves make this app worth it. The only thing I actively want updated about this app is the inability to change the timer to vibrate only. It's my only reliable timer of its type, but I can't use it at school due to the sound. Still, I would and do happily recommend this app.
This app really needs a way to sync with another user.   If only one person in the household is doing this work, that imbalance is part of the problem.
Simple to use and to the point. If you like endless customization, this is not the app for you, but if you just want to get straight to cleaning, this will do it!

All the sub five stars didn't understand the purpose of this app. If you're already motivated to clean, this isn't the app for you. This is an app for depressed people who are so overwhelmed by everything that they don't know where to begin. This will give you a place to start. It's incredible, but it isn't for you if you're already excited to clean your house. Go use a different app.
Great app concept!  Would love to be able to edit built in tasks.

I'm really enjoying using this! I would like to have "conservatory" added to the rooms, that would be good. Also, is there a way of editing the challenges that you have inputted yourself if I feel I need to add more content. Brilliant app. I've also bought the book and just discovered your website too. Thanks for this x
I really like this app. A useful addition would be a 45/15 minute timer as well, because sometimes 20/10 isn't quite long enough.

This could potentially be a GREAT app and is not all bad. But the experience is just meh. The quick challenges are great. They do help to an extent. But the random motivation is only given if you click on it. It would be 1000x better if you randomly got a notification on your phone like "It's 3pm, get off your lazy ass for 5 minutes and scrub the toilet." Is it worth paying for? Eh. I hope it gets better in the future.
Love it!
Used to be free! Also used to have a whole list by room! Lame, want a refund.
Lacks of preset lists. The only app i purchased. I thought it would be better
Not enough instructions prefer Web sitey
Can you make it so points earned get us something cool and how about adding a "challenge" your friend option or "race" your friend type thing! Would be fun!

I loved this when it worked. Now it crashes. If I close it, the timer will STILL go off, and there's no way to turn off the timer without opening it and starting the timer again. Update and fix please! And I will change my rating. Until then DON'T BUY. Waste of money.

I can't figure out how to set intervals on recurring tasks. Emailed support 6 days ago and no response. They have pdfs you can print for certain intervals in the site, but I don't see how to create this in the app.

I love this app! The only reason why I'm giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is because I like my daily routines, and being able to add recurring routines would be awesome. There are already great lists on the site, but not in the app. For my routines, right now I am using UfYH and the FlyLady app together. Will adding recurring routines be something that y'all add in the future?
I can't seem to find a way to set monthly or weekly reminders for recurring tasks I'm setting up. Maybe I'm just missing it.
The ability to set tasks as recurring, with reminders, is great, but I'd like to be able to specify how often they recur (e.g., daily, weekly, monthly, yearly).
A widget would be good, or management from the notification bar. Thanks.
The recurring task option needs a frequency setting, so I can create daily jobs, every other day, weekly, etc. Include that and you get 5 stars.
So far, so good.  I only wish the app would give you credit for EVERY task you complete, not just a special subset of them.

Would be cool if the motivations had sound and actually yelled at you. ;)  I am disappointed in the lack of lists in the app.  Also, once I've cleared my own task it's just gone.  I'd like to be able to see what I've accomplished of my own goals.  Lastly, it would be great if I could edit my tasks after they've been added.  I often throw all the chores in my head into one task but later need to separate them and there doesn't seem to be any editing option.

I like this app!! It goes along great with the website which has great tips for the "motivationally challenged" like myself. Suggestion: a "tips" section for quick access to some of the great tips offered on the website like vinegar cleaning solution, drain volcano, laundry tips etc.
I will restore the rating to five stars when some of the bugs are fixed. Challenges crash every single time and the alarm doesn't go off until the screen is active.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback! This bug is addressed in the newest update (version 1.03).

content: Good idea, bad execution
There should be a prompt to take before and after photos and share them with the other users. Also,  the ability to make and share your custom cleaning routines and lists of chores would be nice.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback!

content: Sometimes I just don't know where to start! This app solves that issue

The only thing I wish for is a 'couples' version. One account, sync it between devices, with the same task list for my husband and I, so it would show when either of us had done something. Could also have a competition mode to see who did the most. Anything to get him to do some housework without being nagged.

Works well but the language is horriblem id seen reports of it being updated and langauge changed on apple products so had hopes on android as well.  Love the app but having to delete as i have children who get on my phone.

Love it but I wish there was a way to set tasks weekly, daily like have an alarm to remind me Wednesday is clean sheet day or a way to set it to times per week like set the bathroom to clean 3x a week.  Other than that love it and love the motivation helps a lot i would love to see an update allowing me to do this I would pay good money for it as a lazy and forgetful person this would save my life
Awesome app! Love it ‚ù§üëçüëç

I would use this app so much more if there wasn't the problem with the notification sound. It will only let me use the same sound as my ringtone. If I try to change the notification sound, it changes the ringtone on my phone. This has been a problem since I first downloaded it and the fact that it still hasn't been fixed is pretty disappointing.

I do like the app, but I have one request. If I'm working to unf*ck a specific room, I'd like the room challenge to remember which room I'm doing.  It's annoying to have it reset to the laundry room each time.

So far, I really like it. But a pause button for the timer would be great. What if I have to pee? Or something more involved than pee? Sometimes that need arises before work time is over, and sometimes we just can't put it off for another 10 or 12 minutes. And really, I don't want to spend my break on the toilet. One other thing: I don't pay for apps. If I can't find something like it, I can do without it. However, a few of my friends said UfYH helped them immensely. So I took the risk. Glad I did!!

I love this app! It's great for keeping me on track when I'm feeling weak but need to keep things tidy. I did notice, however, that after the first cycle of the 20/10 timer, the time just displays as 0:00. The timer still works fine, but it's just an odd thing I noticed. Great app otherwise!
I'd like it a lot better if there was an alarm that randomly went off with a task
It was okay.

As a lazy person, anything that can help lend a little motivation is great. I've only been using this app for a day, but so far I love it. The only thing I wish for is a page that shows me what I've already accomplished. As a traditional "to-do list" writer..everyone gets a little satisfaction from being able to cross something off the list. Overall great app, though

I got a new phone (Galaxy Note 4) and updated all my Android apps. I never had any issues using UFYH on my Nexus 4 or iPad,  but on this phone it's nothing but trouble.  When the alarm goes off it takes 6 or seven screens to turn it off; I even unlocked my screen so it would be easier to get to,  but that didn't help much. There aren't any settings in the app, as far as I can tell,  so I can't adjust things the way I'd like to.
I've found I'd rather "Challenge By Room" also gave an indication of how long the app thinks each task will take. Also premade lists would be handy.
Short stints, plenty of breaks. Add a  rewards system on the fridge and you have your own game! Needs a points system :D

Love that you can make the lists to suit your situation.  It really does help to have the alarm go off.  Can't wait to get my mess clean so I can start working on the challenges! Makes cleaning a game instead of a chore.

I love the app already, but I somehow can't manage to delete tasks from my list. I go to highlight them to delete and they open to edit. I press the garbage can and it goes back to the list view. You aren't giving me false hope, are you?

As stated in other reviews two major flaws are not being able to shut it off until you navigate into the app (why no pop up or something) and also when you change the alarm tone it changes your ring tone also. I will keep the app vs refund because I do like the ufyh methods. Also disappointing that the lists from the website are not automatically on the app . This should be a free app.

I kept it bc it has some really great features, like random task selection/suggestions. The 1 thing holding it back is without the ability to see completed tasks as done in some way, I feel like I have not achieved anything & I can't tell what I have completed from what I haven't or what I need to do that day--the longer the list, the more problematic that is. A strike through, red check mark, or best IMO just have them colour blocked a nice colour & go below uncompleted tasks. This makes the list unusable.
I love how this app gamifies cleaning the house so I can feel like an action adventurer conquering a quest instead of like an overwhelmed working mom :-)
You make your own lists Elle Molina
It keeps force closing and there is no beeper noise or anything when time runs out
I like the way it tackles getting things done but changing the alert tone in the app changes your ringer for all notifications on your phone which is infuriating. Change that and this is easy 5 stars
Love it!

This is a great app for getting things done. My only issue is that on  the 20/10 timer, after the first 20/10, when you hit the "back to work" button, the 20 minute timer shows up as 0:00, and stays that way. You have to cancel the challenge, and restart the timer to do another 20/10. Does anyone else have this problem?

I'd love it if there was a button for a random task from my list. Also, a way to untick irrelevant tasks from the random button that does exist. If i click through too many car or pet tasks i may well end up clicking through stuff i should do rather than getting on with what im told to do! Great concept.
Alarm didn't go off for challenges.  No premade lists. Was expecting a list like the website with a built in timer.
This app is pointless. It doesn't even remind you to do your tasks that you have set reminders for. Uninstalled.
Please add notifications for getting more motivation.

Developers,Pls take a look at fairshare app. I decided to buy this app because I like the blog, and although I like the home screen set up, the idea of random challenges and the motivational words, I hate the way my tasks are set up! I'm fairly certain the order selection at the bottom doesn't work the way it was intended. The notifications don't make noise even though I set it to make noise, and I can't figure out if there's a way to get it to pop up on my screen instead of hiding in my notifications bar.
This app actually gives me more motivation to clean. It makes cleaning more of a game by challenging you. Great purchase!
But, I wish I could decide how long my work/breaks will be. Checklists would be nice, also.

I love the motivation and challenges, but it would be VERY helpful to have editable lists already set up. It takes a lot of time and quickly becomes boring. I think it's safe to say that most of us wanting to use the app have ADD, and we need help getting  organized in the first place.
Love the website and love this app. Makes it way easier to get organized and get motivated to get off my bum. Lists WOULD be nice, like everyone's commented, but I'm happy with it as is too.
Provides random tasks I don't always think of, good at breaking tasks down into manageable portions.

I love the blog, and was hoping for some lists or something like that. All it has is a 'make your own list' type of thing, with no suggestions,  and a timer. Well I don't need to pay a dollar for that. I'm uninstalling, but would gladly reinstall if it was made more like the website with lists and stuff.

That's it, really. Best purchase ever. Simple, easy to use, excellent at keeping you on task. I'm a chronically messy person often struggling with depression, but this helps me work a little bit at a time through it.
Love this app! I have ADHD and it helps me to stay on tasks and actually finish them!
Really love this app. Was on my tablet and just installed on my phone too. Wish I could sync them both though.
Although I don't use it as much as I should it is incredible helpful and worth every penny

Site is awesome. Would like capability to import lists from site as to do lists, and to continually work on to do list using 20 min timer. Currently it starts a separate timer when you go to the next task. Challenges are neat, and the motivation is hilarious!
I recommend this constantly to friends. Love it!
I did my washing up finally!!

I wish this app let you share the list with other people in your family (ie with a Password ) so they can all see the list of tasks that need to be done! Also a few premade lists could be helpful. Please update soon!
The daily/weekly/seasonal/annual checklists on UFyH are the best. No idea why they're not included in the app.

I have this app for my iPad, and I love it, but this version for my android is not working as well. If I set the notification noise, it changes my phone's ringtone. And then no matter what, it plays the same loud beeping, which is difficult to turn off. If you don't leave this app open, it's hard to get to the timer to turn the sound off right away. I do most of my house cleaning while my baby sleeps, so that doesn't work for me at all.

This app is really good. I like that you can set your own lists of tasks that need doing and set them to be recurring. However, when you finish a recurring task there is no record that it has been done. It is not noted in your achievements. I think that an activity summary would be good to acknowledge when the recurring tasks have been completed, how long it took etc.
I will use this.

While there are some set activities that they suggest, the app lacks the structure of the website.  For the most part, this works as a timer, though there are a few suggested activities, sorted by room.  I'd like to see it expand to contain some of the lists for tackling a room (or even just the basic UfY mornings checklist) and maybe incorporate weekly challenges from the blog to keep things fresh.  As it stands, it really isn't worth spending money on.
Like others I wanted lists - but started making my own - then realized later the recurring stuff - can't be set as daily or weekly.

I liked it however: I agree with everyone else and would love the lists that are on the website. And reminders and stuff. Secondly it would be great if you could create an account and store your lists, I did a factory reset, then got a new phone and lost all my progress!
I work well with the 20/10 thing but now,on three different phones,it doesn't work. It'll go one  cycle, but won't do the next one,you have to go back to the the beginning each time. Annoying.
Instead of manually entering things to clean it would be nice to have a database/samples to start with.
Please add the emergency list to this app. Would make it perfect.
Fantastic app, however the 20/10 timer stops working after the first break.
This is the best cleaning app I've found. I absolutely love it!!!

I saw the comments about how you had to put in your own tasks and could deal with that but what I don't understand is why, if you're setting up something that's recurring, it doesn't ask how often you want it to recur? And why, if you set reminder dates on tasks, you can't sort by them chronologically? I might as well use my Google task list!

...is that I can't argue with taking 20 mins out of my busy day of looking at funny cat pictures on the internet to try to improve one area of my house.  And then - it very rarely takes the whole 20 mins, and I always feel so good about getting something done, that I'm motivated to do something else.  There are additional features I'd love to see, like being able to review everything I accomplished in a day, and the ability to edit my tasks, but overall a great app! The motivation button is pure gold! :)

The concept is good and the online support through tumblr & Twitter is nice and encouraging. But the app is buggy. The timer and the alarm are out of sync. When creating a task, it FORCES you to add a description. Clean bathroom means clean bathroom! There's nothing to describe! The timer will act weird. Not really worth $1 at this point but I can see it being so in the future. I also don't like that it messes with your ringtone when you are trying to select a notification sound. This app needs UnF&%^*.
I like that it will yell at me to stop being lazy, because sometimes I need a kick in the pants.
Really disappointed that there were no lists! The app would be worth more time if it had thd lists.

I'm going to email the developer directly and then adjust my rating.  But last year I installed the app on my Samsung Galaxy Tab 8.9, the "dreaded crash bug" referenced in the version updates. It aptly describes what happened next. I can't Uninstall the ufyh app and I haven't been able to use the tablet since. Where and who can I contact for support? I really would love to be able to use my tablet again.
replyContent: We received your email and a reply is on its way!

content: Incredibly helpful tool. Would be happy to donate $$$ to further development. Thank you for all that you do!!

I have difficulty shoring up energy and motivation for even simple chores. In my first day of use, I am really liking the concept. This is great for those who get overwhelmed by long to-do lists. I can promise myself to complete at least one challenge, and that motivates me to do more. Even if it's only one, it's something. I found the timer to be a bit wonky, so I just ignore it.
Good
Love this app. It has lots of useful features. I use it every week when I clean my house!

I'm a pretty neat and clean person, but I have a tendency to clean and clean until I am exhausted. The timer feature helps remind me to slow down and take breaks. Highly recommend! There's a great Tumblr and a blog too!

Everything seems to work correctly. Great job, thank you for all your hard work!    Update, I still love the app but there seems to be an issue with my timer. I can't do multiple 20/10's without exiting app and going back in. It does give me the option but the timer doesn't reset itself.
I love this app. 5-10-20 minute challenges. Make your own to do list. Bluntly motivate me to clean my house. Whats not to love? I needed this

When it is running,  there is no indicator in the notification bar.  If you navigate away from the 20/10 timer,  you have to reopen the app to even find it even when the time goes off.  Really annoying. (galaxy s4).  I also agree that there should be pre-made lists such as on the website. Not paid app level.
Never thought anything could motivate me to clean.  This app is awesome.
Great app.  Great companion to the site.
This app helps me keep on top of my chores and it was great for homework deadlines too! The blog is awesome and very inspirational :)

I have followed UFYH's blog for a long time and it has helped me immensely. The app gave me the extra boast to keep things organized by doing a little at a time on a regular basis. I like that it gives you a list of challenge chores for each room/area. I have never had any crashing/bug problems. I do wish I could drag and drop the challenge chore items to my own to-do list so I don't have to re-type the title/instruction for my to-do list. Other than that, I love it.

I love this app and website and just having the app on my phone has made me force myself to be more productive in my day to day life. My only minor complaint would be that the beep for the timer is a little annoying and it doesn't want to use my ringtone or any other files on my phone, but that's it. I can deal with that. Yay UFYH!
UFYH is like actual MAGIC and now I have it portably, even with my WIFI off. I've encouraged others to buy it (it is my ONLY paid for app) because it is so good
My favourite app of all time. Has helped heaps with my hoarding tendencies! :-)

OK, I've only just downloaded this app, but I did so based on your website, which contains lots of lists etc. I realise that everyone is different, but I was rather disappointed to see that you have to add your own lists for recurring tasks. I was hoping that there would be default lists that could be edited and ticked off etc. I want to follow your emergency list, but i'll have to do that just by browsing your website from my phone. Unless i setup my own lists, i'm guessing i don't get reminders either - which is part of my problem, I need reminding to do anything :(

I really do like the set up of this app. I love the concept, and the blog is AWESOME.  that being said, I do wish I could sync it to my tablet, or with my roommate so we could be on the same page. but no worries, I can just re type it on theirs.  Does anyone know how to change the timer though? I change it, but when it goes off, it's still just beeps. Any ideas?
Love this app. Would be good if there was a choice of 20/10 or 45/15 timer.
Works great for me. When I notice the house getting crazy, I pick a random challenge or challenge by room and go. Big help!
It's really useful, but my rooms are very different from the list, and I'd like to be able to name them.
I've had this app for a few days. It comes highly recommended and it is the only app I have ever paid for.  My only disappointment is that it won't sync across my devices (tablet and phone).

Only suggestion: when the 20/10 timer is done,  can it be fixed to begin a new round? When my break is done the app says "back to work" but the clock doesn't reset for another round.    But overall this app is awesome!

My only request is to fix the notification sound so it is not linked with the phone call notification. When my 20 mins are up, it defaults to my ringtone, which always confuses me. But, when I change it in app, my actual ringtone gets changed, too.

What a life-saver for us regular humans who aren't very good/suck/are horrible at keeping our homes clean. Much like the Tumblr site, this app shows you any task can be broken down into manageable chunks. I like the by-room challenges, and though I hate it, I use the timer and the room challenges to get dishes done and bed made, because "excuses are boring."  Incredibly useful, and a bargain at $1.99.
Actually helps me do the stuff I put off until it's overwhelming. Thanks so much!
I love this app. So awesome and actually motivates me to get stuff done. The only app I have ever paid for and it was well worth. Updated my review to 5 stars after the last bug fix

Minor thing makes the review 4/5 at this time -- I'm not sure if it's just my Android 2.2 phone, but when I'm doing a sequence of 20/10s, the first "20" will show the countdown (20:00, 19:59, 19:58, etc.), but the subsequent 20s only display 0:00, though the progress bar and the timer do still work.
It's the only app I've ever paid for.
Great app. Love the 20/10 timer and the random challenges help if you are a bit bored with the daily routine.
This is the best app in the whole app store.  A steal at twice the price!
I love the blog and love this app! It helps me stay motivated to do what I need to do. Thank you!
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback!

content: Timers and lists and motivation oh my!

content: It is just what I need - unfortunately it crashes every time I try to use it. Very frustrating Samsung Note 2 user

content: I like the app for the random challenges. Finally tried the 20/10 timer, and it rang with my phone-call ringtone - not acceptable. So I went in and changed it to a unique tone; that worked, it was great. Moved on with my life. Phone rang...with the tone I'd set for UFYH! That is not acceptable. It really needs to have its own sound - and it certainly shouldn't be changing my standard ringtone! I won't be using the timer until that's fixed (using a modified Pomodoro timer instead - it doesn't track with UFYH, but at least I can tell what's ringing right off).
This app motivated me to clean my utensil drawer and it made me feel hope.

I really like the challenges and the star system, bit there is one thing that works make this perfect: upload the cleaning checklists from the site!  I would love to just have the daily, weekly, monthly checklists already put into the app  instead of printing out the PDF and probably recycling it by accident.
Has helped me clean one step at a time.
Doesn't record any achievements. Just another reminder "nothing" is done
replyContent: The achievements are recorded after every five completed random challenges, or when you've completed your entire to-do list (excluding recurring tasks). Thanks for your feedback!

content: It's a good app. Only thing I do not like are the motivations, the caps make them sound aggressive and yelly rather than encouraging.  The challenges and to-do lists are good.
Such a great approach, and app to pair with it.

Every time I used it it crashes. It doesn't motivate me if I'm just miserable because my efforts aren't being logged...and no a tidy home doesn't help because that's fleeting. It's gone faster than I can clean it. I wanted to see my accomplishments recorded.
replyContent: We're working on a fix for the crash bug and should have it out soon. Thanks for your feedback!

content: This combined with the blog is the best you can do for yourself if you struggle with anything to do with cleaning
Had been rated at one star because it wouldn't open. Now it works and I love it!
replyContent: The update that fixes that just posted! Thanks for all of your help with assisting us in tracking down that bug. Let us know what you think of the app now!

content: I love the app. I love the idea of the app. I love the challenges and my house is looking a lot better.... but what the point of the challenge timer if it doesn't make a noise when it goes off? (The 10/20 timer uses my ringtone, but the "random challenge" and room-specific challenges make no noise.)
Clever way to get things done.

I finally managed to sort out the huge chunk of mess that is my bedroom thanks to this app! The motivational lines are really funny, and the challenges are excellent. Would like to be able to set tasks to reoccur daily, weekly and monthly.
My list crashes every time I try to use.  I can turn it on but when I click button to complete task it locks up.
replyContent: We're looking into that and are hoping to have a fix soon!

content: This app's attitude is direct and no bs. It doesn't get cutesy about otherwise uninspiring tasks. It just tells you to do it. Cleaning is already annoying. The app has customized to do lists, random challenges of varying lengths in various rooms. And it gives you cred when you do your stuff often enough. Aligns with the site and tumbr of the same name. We'll worth the pittance it costs.
excellent. a boon to humankind.
Love the blog, love this app. The timed challenges are great as are the timers. Worth the small investment!

UFYH has, in the years I've been following it, completely changed how I  approach both cleaning and maintaining my household. I'm pretty sure I'd still being living out of boxes from my June move without the mental shift that comes with reading the blog.   The app is great at maintaining the tone and mood of the original blog. I've used it to kick-start some cleaning, and I've used it to keep up a to-do list.

Simple and effective motivating app. You can take different approaches - putting in a to-do list, or selecting a challenge by time it takes or room - and the longest it expects you to work is 20 mins, with 10 min breaks. You can also pause tasks which is helpful if you do need to work for shorter stretches. Straight-forward, makes things better.
The UFYH app is fantastic. The system works well for me, and the app gives me just the motivation I need. Love it.

great app at kicking your butt to get some work done. the random motivation tool is cool :) the random challenge is very useful too! yeah, a couple of features like allowing the timer to run in the background would be good, cos when i read messages on my phone, the timer stops and i have to reset the timer thingy. otherwise, great app! good job!!!

But we have GOT to be able to add the chalenges directly to our lists. Seriously. My entire list will be the challenges.  If I had time (or motivation) to think out and write a list, I wouldn't need the app! If not from the challenges, then at least a pr-loaded selection to simply pick a bunch of tasks from in order to build lists. Another idea, app-generated lists, perhaps based on need, or speed, or type, or... anything; like a challenge list,  which can be crossed off as completed. I need you, UFYH!

This app does so much to help me break chores down and stay on top of them. I second others who say that an undo/edit feature would be a great addition. Likewise, I would be over the moon for more "recurring" options - for example, to be able to set laundry as a task every Thursday automatically. Then it would really be perfect.
Best app that i found to  motivate me to clean
This app is a life saver!
Love the randomness of this app. Just what I've been looking for.

I uninstalled and was going to reinstall but had forgotten I paid for the app :( so, I'll keep checking back for bug fix.  Just wanna let you know that's happening, because I really like the app, but really need the timer to work right.  The r

really like this app and ufyh philisophy.  i like having these tasks separate from the rest of my day. i do wish recurrences could be variable so that i could  schedule the ufyh checklists. then i could schedule monthly, weekly, etc chores. then for sure a perfect app. keep up the good work!
You are awesome
So happy to have an app and not just a blog. Love the 20/10 timer.
Awesome app, awesome system. It is possible to get a handle on household chores.
Love it.

The philosophy behind this app is excellent: do no more than what you can. 20 minutes, 15, 3. Take breaks and don't pull a marathon. No need to "clean all the things". Also, your house is yours: don't clean for visits but for you and what you want and like.
Like having the blog in "to do list" format, but the Android app constantly freezes and crashes my phone.
replyContent: If you update to the newest version, that bug should be resolved. Thanks for your feedback!

content: A great motivator. One of the few apps I'd actually pay for. It does sometimes make my phone crash, though, requiring a battery pull. Hopefully that'll be fixed soon.

content: Only thing it is missing is daily/weekly repeating list.

content: I love the potential here. Must have improvements: ability to randomize the user created tasks & to set up recurring tasks. Let's do this!
replyContent: Great news! The newest update includes recurring tasks. Let us know how you like it!

content: I would like a notification bar icon so that when my alarm goes off and I'm in another app, I can easily silence it.
Doing the five minute challenges has already made my house cleaner!

While the system is basically a modified pomodoro, what makes UFYH so wonderful is the attitude behind it. Happy to see the Android version of the app at last (if only so that the blogger doesn't go crazy with people asking about it any more)
I've waited so long and it's here and it's amazing!

Have been following the website for over a year, and it really changed my concept about housework/chores. In that it moved it from being a 'drudge' (in my headspace) to one of 'maintenance'. Just as how you can take twenty minutes in the morning to get ready, you can do that for your house too. Or, there's the option of a five minute random task, to see how much you can get done in five minutes- you'd be surprised how much can be done in five minutes! In twenty minutes, I have half the house done (swept, wiped down and dusted).  In the first day of getting the app, I managed to clear a desk that had six years of make up samples, papers, books (I'm talking geological layers, people).   The only drawback is that when you try to do long term lists (the first option of things to do, high priority to low), the application freezes and you need to force close.   Overall though, this is the app to get if you're overwhelmed by the thought of housework. Download the app, do a random five minute challenge (your computer desk, tidy your bed), and feel you attitude towards housework change. "You are better than your mess," and with this app, you believe it.
replyContent: The latest update should fix the force close issue for you and adds recurring tasks. Let us know what you think!

content: Bought this app purely on a friend's recommendation and the tumblr feed.  I've not used it properly yet but it's already making me chuckle.

Bought this because I love your tumblr and the way you talk about and deconstruct gender and gender identity. Thank you for always working to be inclusive and holding yourself accountable when something could have been phrased or said better. I truly appreciate it.
Yay, the android app is here!
Thanks, Cleaning Witch!

This app is perfect if you struggle with procrastination, perfectionism, laziness, overwhelmed-ness... really anything that keeps you from being the neat person you'd theoretically like to be. I love how the 20-10 timer is slightly difficult to futz with - it prevents me from fudging my timer times and either slacking off or marathon-cleaning (which ends in me being too wiped to maintain for a few days at which point it's a mess again). The to-do list is easy to customize and the app gives you just enough feedback "good job" type stuff to be motivating without feeling patronizing in the least. I HIGHLY recommend it if you're not a naturally neat person.

¬£1.25 for an app of this fabulousness is an absolute bargain. I've been following UfYH on tumblr for just about ever and it has been life changing. I'm really glad the android app is finally here! Plus we get extra swears, which I think makes the wait worthwhile.
Super excited to see this finally available. Loyal tumblr follower.

I like the concept, and this would get five stars if you add one feature. I need to be reminded to do things automatically on weekly, monthly and daily basis. For example, clean the cat box every week! The reminders seem to only be a one time basis.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback! The newest update includes recurring tasks! Let us know what you think!

content: UfYH is one of my most-frequented sites on the internet, because it's incredibly inspiring to see what people are able to accomplish. There are few things as satisfying as an organized room, and -- sometimes -- few things more difficult to maintain. This helps. I'm so excited to have the app available on android.
Considering how motivating the website has been, this app should be a huge boost for me.

UfYH has changed how I think about cleaning my apartment.  It's made a huge difference in my life, and that's not an exaggeration.  I'm looking forward to seeing how the app makes things even better--it's great so far!
Thank you so so much, you wonderful person (and many wonderful helpers)! You have removed my very last boring excuse :)
Great app and well worth the wait. Thanks for all the hard work getting it out! Only issue I've found: app force-closes when trying to set a reminder for tasks.

content: Portable Kick-Up-Butt

I've been following UFYH on Tumblr for a while now, and I am more than happy to buy the app and support a wonderful person's service to the world. Keep on rockin'! (Haven't had any problems with the app whatsoever, either.)

content: I'm glad this app is finally here!  First time I've ever paid for an app and it's well worth the money.  An easy way to organize all of your life & household chores with reminders and timers.  No technical glitches thus far. ""Terrifying motivation for lazy people with messy homes.""  Maybe not so terrifying, more motivating!
I'm very excited to start using the app as soon as I get home. Everything is manageable when you do it in small doses.

Easy to use and navigate. The random challenge is doing a great job of getting me motivated. Ufyh is a much better suited method of housekeeping for me than traditional methods. It's making me feel a lot better about my home and my space.
This is an excellent app for making life that much easier. Clear, easy to use and wonderfully motivational. An instant hit.
It's a great way to get moving and get organized in a way that'll keep you sane. Well worth the purchase.
Right now, there still seems to be a few glitches; it's crashing when you try to make your to do list. Overall, though,I love it!

content: The basic philosophy is that anything can get clean in small manageable bites, and it works on all areas of life. So great!
I'm messy by nature. The UfYH system is the only thing that has ever worked for me.
This is the only reason I have a clean house
This is a well-designed and easy to use housecleaning app that isn't fluffy, twee or fru-fru.  Love it.

I love the entire UfYH philosophy, and the app makes my life so much easier. Plenty of features, and all of them seem to work correctly. I especially love the motivational messages, which keep me laughing while I work.
